  "text": "In terms of surgical creation, wait times from referral to fistula creation in countries with higher prevalent fistula rates, Italy, Germany and Japan, ranged from 5 to 6 days while it was 40-43 days in the UK and Canada, where fistula prevalence is lower [CITATION_1] . Although the delay in surgical creation is much shorter in the USA than in Canada (7 vs 25 days), more American nephrologists indicated surgical consultation delay to be a barrier (50 vs 38%).",
